        "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\ngit revert 240bbdbdc76e0e91af9f18164eadb2708d14c6fb -m 1\n\nThe 240bbdbdc.. is the \"merged\" commit to back up.\n\nThe \"-m 1\" is the first commit from the \"merge:\" line when you do a git log in the merged commit, ie. \n\n--\ncommit 240bbdbdc76e0e91af9f18164eadb2708d14c6fb\nMerge: 3ee69f1 a97e1ea\nAuthor: Jorge Hernandez <jh1730@att.com>\nDate:   Fri Jul 13 14:05:15 2018 +0000\n\n    Merge \"fix try block\"\n--\n\nNote \"Merge: 3ee69f1 a97e1ea\"\n\nif you do a git log on 3ee69f1 and 3ee69f1 ..would want to back out to the first which is Mike's one, hence the \"-m 1\".   The \"-m 1\" disambiguate it to the right one.\n\nThen I did the usual I do:\n\ngit commit -as --amend - to add Issue-ID and git review",
        "patchset_number": 2
      },
